en Book,' 'Vice' Among Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-casting-society-artios-award-winners-full-list-1173402 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 1, 2019 |date=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\"|<center>'''Season 2'''</center>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"27\"| <center>2019</center>\n| [[American Cinema Editors Awards 2019|American Cinema Editors Awards]]\n| Best Edited Drama Series for Non-Commercial Television\n| Cindy Mollo and Heather Goodwin Floyd (for \"One Way Out\")\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Giardina |first=Carolyn |title='Bohemian Rhapsody,' 'The Favourite' Top Editors' ACE Eddie Awards |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/american-cinema-editors-eddie-award-winners-list-1174337 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 2, 2019 |date=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Art Directors Guild Awards 2018|Art Directors Guild Awards]]\n| Excellence in Production Design for a One-Hour Contemporary Single-Camera Television Series\n| [[Derek R. Hill]] (for \"The Gold Coast\")\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Giardina |first=Carolyn |title=Art Directors Guild Awards: 'Favourite,' 'Black Panther,' 'Crazy Rich Asians' Among Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/art-directors-guild-awards-winners-list-2019-1174313 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 3, 2019 |date=February 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Cinema Audio Society Awards]]\n| [[Cinema Audio Society Award for Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for Television Series \u2013 One Hour|Outstanding Achievement in Sound Mixing for Television Series \u2013 One Hour]]\n| Felipe Borrero, Larry B. Benjamin, [[Kevin Valentine]], Phillip McGowan, Matt Hovland, and David Torres (for \"The Badger\")\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |title=CAS Awards: 'Black Panther', 'A Star Is Born' & 'Mrs. Maisel' Among Cinema Audio Society Nominees |url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/cas-awards-2019-nominations-black-panther-a-star-is-born-marvelous-mrs-maisel-cinema-audio-society-nominees-1202531016/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 8, 2019 |date=January 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[9th Critics' Choice Television Awards|Critics' Choice Television Awards]]\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Best Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]]\n| [[Julia Garner]]\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Crist |first=Allison |title=Critics' Choice Awards: 'Roma,' 'Americans,' 'Mrs. Maisel' Top Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-critics-choice-awards-winners-list-full-1172261 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=January 13, 2019 |date=January 13, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[71st Directors Guild of America Awards|Directors Guild of America Awards]]\n| [[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Drama Series|Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Dramatic Series]]\n| Jason Bateman (for \"Reparations\")\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Handel |first=Jonathan |title='Roma's' Alfonso Cuaron Takes Top Honor at DGA Awards |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/dga-awards-2019-winners-list-full-1178563 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 3, 2019 |date=February 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Gold Derby Awards\n| Best Drama Actor\n| Jason Bateman\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2019/gold-derby-tv-awards-2019-nominations-game-of-thrones-veep-news/ |title=Gold Derby TV Awards 2019 nominations: 'Game of Thrones' and 'Veep' lead, while 'Pose' is the top new show of the year |last= |first= |date=July 24, 2019 |publisher=GoldDerby |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Drama Actress\n| Laura Linney\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Supporting Actress\n| Julia Garner\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[76th Golden Globe Award