{"title_page": "Agim Ademi", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name          = Agim Ademi\n|image         = \n|image_size    = \n|caption       = \n|order         = President of\n|office        = Football Federation of Kosovo\n|term_start    = 6 July 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ffk-kosova.com/presidenti-i-ffk-se/|title=\"Presidenti i FFK-s\u00eb\"|trans-title=\u201cPresident of FFK\u201d|publisher=FFK Kosova|language=Albanian|date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n|term_end      = \n|predecessor   = [[Fadil Vokrri]]\n|successor     = \n|birth_name    = Agim Ademi\n|birth_date    = {{birth date|1961|10|19|df=y}}\n|birth_place   = [[Pristina]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n|death_date    = \n|death_place   = \n|height        =\n|nationality   = [[Kosovo Albanian]]\n|occupation    = [[Footballer]]<br />Football administrator\n|signature     =\n|signature_alt =\n|module        =\n{{Infobox football biography |embed = yes |header-color = lavender\n|position      = \n|youthyears1   = \n|years1        = \n|totalcaps     = \n|nationalyears1 = \n|club-update = \n|nationalteam-update = \n}}\n}}\n\n'''Agim Ademi''' (born 19 October 1961) is a football administrator and former player. He is president of the [[Football Federation of Kosovo]] from 6 July 2018.\n\n==Personal life==\nAgim Ademi is married and is living in [[Pristina]]. He studied Science in Homeland Security and Emergency Management.\n\n==Career==\nFrom 1975 until 1988 was an active footballer.\n\n==Football Federation of Kosovo==\nFrom 2000 until 6 July 2018, he made his contribution as Vice President of the [[Football Federation of Kosovo]], and from that day he was entrusted with the post of President of the Football Federation of Kosovo, where he was unanimously voted by 58 delegates to the Extraordinary Electoral Assembly, with four-year term 2018-2022, as the position of president had remained vacant following the death of [[Fadil Vokrri]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ademi, Agim}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kosovan footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=December 2019}}\n{{more citations needed|date=October 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name          = Agim Ademi\n|image         = \n|image_size    = \n|caption       = \n|order         = President of\n|office        = Football Federation of Kosovo\n|term_start    = 6 July 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ffk-kosova.com/presidenti-i-ffk-se/|title=\"Presidenti i FFK-s\u00eb\"|trans-title=\u201cPresident of FFK\u201d|publisher=FFK Kosova|language=Albanian|date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n|term_end      = \n|predecessor   = [[Fadil Vokrri]]\n|successor     = \n|birth_name    = Agim Ademi\n|birth_date    = {{birth date|1961|10|19|df=y}}\n|birth_place   = [[Pristina]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n|death_date    = \n|death_place   = \n|height        =\n|nationality   = [[Kosovo Albanian]]\n|occupation    = [[Footballer]]<br />Football administrator\n|signature     =\n|signature_alt =\n|module        =\n{{Infobox football biography |embed = yes |header-color = lavender\n|position      = \n|youthyears1   = \n|years1        = \n|totalcaps     = \n|nationalyears1 = \n|club-update = \n|nationalteam-update = \n}}\n}}\n\n'''Agim Ademi''' (born 19 October 1961) is a football administrator and former player. He is president of the [[Football Federation of Kosovo]] from 6 July 2018.\n\n==Personal life==\nAgim Ademi is married and is living in [[Pristina]]. He studied Science in Homeland Security and Emergency Management.\n\n==Career==\nFrom 1975 until 1988 was an active footballer.\n\n==Football Federation of Kosovo==\nFrom 2000 until 6 July 2018, he made his contribution as Vice President of the [[Football Federation of Kosovo]], and from that day he was entrusted with the post of President of the Football Federation of Kosovo, where he was unanimously voted by 58 delegates to the Extraordinary Electoral Assembly, with four-year term 2018-2022, as the position of president had remained vacant following the death of [[Fadil Vokrri]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ademi, Agim}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kosovan footballers]]\n", "name_user": "Keskkonnakaitse", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agim_Ademi"}
